<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

Extend the generic ELFStreamer class so that it can emit mapping symbols at the appropriate points in the object files.

These symbols are defined in the <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm">ARM</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/elf">ELF</a> ABI: infocenter.arm.com/help/topic/com.arm.../IHI0044D&#95;aaelf.pdf.

In brief: $a, $t or $d should be emitted at the start of each contiguous region of <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/arm">ARM</a> code, Thumb code or data in a section. In practice, this emission does not rely on explicit assembler directives but on inherent properties of the directives doing the emission (e.g. &quot;.byte&quot; is data, &quot;add
r0, r0, r0&quot; an instruction).

As a result this system is orthogonal to the DataRegion infrastructure used by <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/macho">MachO</a>. Beware!

### emitSymbolAttribute() {#a51936e8a709df3a1eec3e749b2e17e59}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;ARMELFStreamer.cpp&#125;::ARMELFStreamer::emitSymbolAttribute (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsymbol">MCSymbol</a> &#42; Symbol, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#af74c787f7a33e251485729416d260243">MCSymbolAttr</a> Attribute)</>}
  labels = {["inline", "virtual"]}>
If a label is defined before the .type directive sets the label&#39;s type then the label can&#39;t be recorded as thumb function when the label is defined.

We override <a href="#a51936e8a709df3a1eec3e749b2e17e59">emitSymbolAttribute()</a> which is called as part of the parsing of .type so that if the symbol has already been defined we can record the label as Thumb. FIXME: there is a corner case where the state is changed in between the label definition and the .type directive, this is not expected to occur in practice and handling it would require the backend to track IsThumb for every label.
